President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Michael Adler as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of South Sudan. Adler is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service with over three decades of experience. He has served on the National Security Council (NSC) staff as the Deputy Senior Director for South Asia and as the Director for Afghanistan. Adler has also held various positions at the State Department, including Acting Deputy Assistant Secretary for South and Central Asian Affairs and Director of the Office of Afghanistan Affairs. He has had overseas assignments in Lebanon, Kuwait, Afghanistan, Iraq, Bosnia and Herzegovina, France, and Qatar.

Additionally, President Biden intends to nominate John Godfrey as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Sudan. Godfrey is currently the Acting Counterterrorism Coordinator and Acting Special Envoy to the Global Coalition to Defeat ISIS in the Counterterrorism Bureau at the U.S. Department of State. He has previously served as the Principal Deputy Coordinator and Deputy Coordinator for Regional and Multilateral Affairs in the Counterterrorism Bureau. Godfrey has also held positions at the U.S. Embassy in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and served as Chief of Staff to the Deputy Secretary of State. His other assignments include roles in Vienna, Baghdad, Libya, Ashgabat, and Damascus. Godfrey holds a Bachelor's Degree from the University of California, Los Angeles, and a Master's Degree in Middle East Studies from the University of Michigan. He is fluent in Arabic.